@page "/docs"

<section class="page-hero bg-light py-5">
    <div class="container">
        <h1 class="display-5 fw-bold">Documentation hub</h1>
        <p class="lead">Everything you need to connect, validate, and monitor APIs with ApiTester.</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="py-5">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row g-4">
            <div class="col-lg-8">
                <div class="doc-section">
                    <h2 class="h4 fw-bold">Getting started</h2>
                    <ol class="doc-list">
                        <li>Connect your first API spec (OpenAPI, GraphQL, or gRPC gateway).</li>
                        <li>Import existing Postman collections or create scenarios from scratch.</li>
                        <li>Schedule recurring monitors and attach alerts to your team channels.</li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
                <div class="doc-section">
                    <h2 class="h4 fw-bold">Guides</h2>
                    <ul class="list-unstyled">
                        <li class="mb-2">Release Readiness Checklist</li>
                        <li class="mb-2">Contract Testing Best Practices</li>
                        <li class="mb-2">Monitoring Playbooks for Incident Response</li>
                        <li class="mb-2">Migrating from legacy API testing suites</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="doc-section">
                    <h2 class="h4 fw-bold">API reference</h2>
                    <p>Developers can automate provisioning, manage environments, and sync results through the ApiTester REST API. The reference covers auth, pagination, and rate limits.</p>
                    <a class="btn btn-outline-primary" href="/contact">Request API access</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-4">
                <div class="doc-sidebar">
                    <h3 class="h6 text-uppercase">Popular topics</h3>
                    <ul class="list-unstyled">
                        <li class="mb-2">Environment variables</li>
                        <li class="mb-2">CI/CD integrations</li>
                        <li class="mb-2">Security configuration</li>
                        <li class="mb-2">Test data management</li>
                    </ul>
                    <img class="img-fluid rounded-4 mt-4" src="images/pattern-grid.svg" alt="" />
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
